---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
    <article class="portfolio-item">
        <div class="img portfolio-img">
            <picture>
                <source media="(min-width: 1200px)" srcset="/images/portfolio/desktop/image-portfolio-manage.jpg 540w,
                                /images/portfolio/desktop/image-portfolio-manage@2x.jpg 1080w" sizes="38w" />

                <source media="(min-width: 768px)" srcset="/images/portfolio/tablet/image-portfolio-manage.jpg 339w,
                                /images/portfolio/tablet/image-portfolio-manage@2x.jpg 678w" sizes="44vw" />

                <source srcset="/images/portfolio/mobile/image-portfolio-manage.jpg 311w,
                                /images/portfolio/mobile/image-portfolio-manage@2x.jpg 622w" />

                <img src="/images/portfolio/desktop/image-portfolio-manage.jpg" alt="">
            </picture>
        </div>
        <div class="portfolio-content">
            <h1 class="h2">Manage</h1>
            <p>
                This project required me to build a fully responsive landing page to the designs provided. I used HTML5,
                along with CSS Grid and JavaScript for the areas that required interactivity, such as the testimonial
                slider.
            </p>
            <div>
                <a class="button__secondary" href="/portfolio/manage">
                    <span class="button__text">View Project</span>
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </article>

    <article class="portfolio-item--flipped">
        <div class="img portfolio-img">
            <picture>
                <source media="(min-width: 1200px)" srcset="/images/portfolio/desktop/image-portfolio-bookmark.jpg 540w,
                                /images/portfolio/desktop/image-portfolio-bookmark@2x.jpg 1080w" sizes="38w" />

                <source media="(min-width: 768px)" srcset="/images/portfolio/tablet/image-portfolio-bookmark.jpg 339w,
                                /images/portfolio/tablet/image-portfolio-bookmark@2x.jpg 678w" sizes="44vw" />

                <source srcset="/images/portfolio/mobile/image-portfolio-bookmark.jpg 311w,
                                /images/portfolio/mobile/image-portfolio-bookmark@2x.jpg 622w" />

                <img src="/images/portfolio/desktop/image-portfolio-bookmark.jpg" alt="">
            </picture>
        </div>
        <div class="portfolio-content">
            <h1 class="h2">Bookmark</h1>
            <p>
                This project required me to build a fully responsive landing page to the designs provided. I used HTML5,
                along with CSS Grid and JavaScript for the areas that required interactivity, such as the features
                section.
            </p>
            <div>
                <a class="button__secondary" href="/portfolio/bookmark">
                    <span class="button__text">View Project</span>
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </article>

    <article class="portfolio-item">
        <div class="img portfolio-img">
            <picture>
                <source media="(min-width: 1200px)" srcset="/images/portfolio/desktop/image-portfolio-insure.jpg 540w,
                                /images/portfolio/desktop/image-portfolio-insure@2x.jpg 1080w" sizes="38w" />

                <source media="(min-width: 768px)" srcset="/images/portfolio/tablet/image-portfolio-insure.jpg 339w,
                                /images/portfolio/tablet/image-portfolio-insure@2x.jpg 678w" sizes="44vw" />

                <source srcset="/images/portfolio/mobile/image-portfolio-insure.jpg 311w,
                                /images/portfolio/mobile/image-portfolio-insure@2x.jpg 622w" />

                <img src="/images/portfolio/desktop/image-portfolio-insure.jpg" alt="">
            </picture>
        </div>
        <div class="portfolio-content">
            <h1 class="h2">Insure</h1>
            <p>
                This was a small project which mostly consisted of HTML and CSS. I built a fully-responsive landing
                page. The only JavaScript this project required was to enable the toggling of the mobile navigation.
            </p>
            <div>
                <a class="button__secondary" href="/portfolio/insure">
                    <span class="button__text">View Project</span>
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </article>

    <article class="portfolio-item--flipped">
        <div class="img portfolio-img">
            <picture>
                <source media="(min-width: 1200px)" srcset="/images/portfolio/desktop/image-portfolio-fylo.jpg 540w,
                                /images/portfolio/desktop/image-portfolio-fylo@2x.jpg 1080w" sizes="38w" />

                <source media="(min-width: 768px)" srcset="/images/portfolio/tablet/image-portfolio-fylo.jpg 339w,
                                /images/portfolio/tablet/image-portfolio-fylo@2x.jpg 678w" sizes="44vw" />

                <source srcset="/images/portfolio/mobile/image-portfolio-fylo.jpg 311w,
                                /images/portfolio/mobile/image-portfolio-fylo@2x.jpg 622w" />

                <img src="/images/portfolio/desktop/image-portfolio-fylo.jpg" alt="">
            </picture>
        </div>
        <div class="portfolio-content">
            <h1 class="h2">Fylo</h1>
            <p>
                This project was built in pure HTML and CSS. I had mobile and desktop designs to work to and built it so
                that it was fully-responsive. I took a mobile-first approach and used modern CSS like Flexbox and Grid
                for layout purposes.
            </p>
            <div>
                <a class="button__secondary" href="/portfolio/fylo">
                    <span class="button__text">View Project</span>
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </article>
</Layout>